summaries:
Here is a summary of the lesson:

- Lesson: Introduction to Queue Data Structure
• A queue is a data structure that follows the First-In-First-Out (FIFO) principle, where elements are added to the end and removed from the front.
• The size and capacity of a queue refer to the number of elements currently in the queue and the maximum number of elements it can hold, respectively.
• Operations on a queue include enqueue (adding an element), dequeue (removing an element), peek (returning the front element without removing it), size, isEmpty, and isFull.
